A FLEET of new buses is transporting pupils to additional support schools thanks to a £1.6million investment. £1.6m boost delivers new school buses A FLEET of new buses is transporting pupils to additional support schools thanks to a £1.6million investment.The 19 Iveco 26-seater vehicles were bought by North Lanarkshire Council.After consultation with parents and schools, the new buses are white and have no council logo to blend in with other traffic.Councillor Jim Logue, Convener of the Learning and Leisure Services Committee, said: &quot;We have listened to pupils, parents and teachers.&quot; 